<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Adolphus M. Dudley graduated from the University of Michigan earning his bachelor's degree in electrical engineering in 1902 and his master's degree in 1931. From 1904 to 1944, he was employed at the Westinghouse Electrical and Manufacturing Company.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The Dudley papers include correspondence, lectures, biographical information, and other records pertaining to his career at Westinghouse.</p>
</scopecontent>

